<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8992&amp;p=95271#p95271"><![CDATA[
There are both series-cut (S in the part number, usually) and parallel-cut(-number in the part number) crystals. Despite being nominally set for the same frequency, if they operated in the wrong mode they be off by many parts per thousand. (Also, what infiniteneslives said)<br /><br />Whether that's enough to be the reason the color component was rejected by your TV's color killer, I don't know.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sun Jun 10, 2012 11:47 am</p><hr />
